Okay, here is a short story for UK children, under 200 words, using UK English and simple words.

---

My Favourite Rainbow

I like the rainbows that come after a soft rain. Not the big, loud ones that shout across the sky. I like the quiet ones.

They appear when the sun peeks out from behind a grey cloud, just a little bit. The rain is still falling, but gently, like tiny silver beads. And there, low in the sky, is my rainbow.

It’s not always bright. Sometimes it’s pale, like a washed-out crayon. A soft pink, a shy blue, a gentle green. It doesn’t stretch from one end of the world to the other. It’s just a small, happy arc, hovering over the garden fence or the old oak tree.

I stand very still, holding my mum’s hand. We don’t say anything. We just watch. The colours shimmer, like they’re made of light and hope. It feels like the sky is giving us a secret hug.

When it fades, I don’t feel sad. I know it will come back. After the next soft rain, when the sun remembers to smile. That’s the rainbow I like best. The quiet, kind one that says, “Look, the sun is still here.”

(Word count: 148) [end of text]


